                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Hand a: 18th or 19th century. Hand b: 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of sections of Text I;
                           elements of the punctuation signs.
 On the first folio of Text I
                           (fol. 3r), two lines are rubricated (alternation with a black line).
                           Rubricated words in Text II are not readable.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="3ra" to="6rb">3ra-6rb</locus>.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus from="7ra" to="8vb">7ra-8vb</locus>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude drawing of the Virgin in blue pen, with the legend Kidanä mǝḥrät "Covenant of Mercy": <locus target="#1v">fol.  1v</locus>. - Two crude crosses drawn in pencil: <locus target="#3r">fol.  3r</locus>. - Crude note written in pencil: <locus target="#2r">fol.  2r</locus>. - Cue for the rubricator (?) written in the upper margin, <locus target="#3r">fol.  3r</locus>: በዘሠለስቱ፡ ዲናር፡ ወይቤል፡. - Doodles: fols. 6v, 9r, 9v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Fragments of three different codices collected and put
                           together, without having been sewn together.
 ff. 1-2 and 9 are
                           protective leaves and are still attached to the wooden board.
 <locus from="3ra" to="6rb">3ra-6rb</locus> are sewn together (overcasting).
                           
 <locus from="7ra" to="8vb">7ra-8vb</locus> is one loose
                           bifolio.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">None.</decoNote>
                     </binding>
